00:26:36,532 --> 00:26:39,752
So, setting games in our world.

420
00:26:40,513 --> 00:26:44,534
So the primary issues that we have with the real world when it comes to content,

421
00:26:44,994 --> 00:26:48,235
number one is augmentation, and I'm going to give an example of all of these things.

422
00:26:48,655 --> 00:26:52,436
So augmentation is like taking something that actually exists and adding to it,

423
00:26:52,876 --> 00:26:54,676
like adding some fictional elements to it.

424
00:26:55,417 --> 00:26:57,259
Accuracy, of course, is what it says.

425
00:26:57,319 --> 00:26:59,260
Like, is the character accurate?

426
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,481
Is that building accurate?

427
00:27:00,561 --> 00:27:02,964
Is that event accurate, the historical event?

428
00:27:04,024 --> 00:27:07,207
Interpretation, so how different cultures interpret

429
00:27:07,267 --> 00:27:11,351
a real world thing, whether it's a gesture,

430
00:27:11,371 --> 00:27:13,733
you know, like this gesture, it means different things

431
00:27:13,773 --> 00:27:14,494
in different countries.

